- literature survey
    - https://arxiv.org/pdf/2408.02946
    - https://arxiv.org/pdf/2502.17424
      https://arxiv.org/pdf/2506.11618
    Machiavelli benchmark
    agentic misalignment
    Betley et al., Emergent Misalignment (arXiv:2502.17424) — the foundational paper, if not already on your list of 16.
    Arditi et al., Refusal in Language Models Is Mediated by a Single Direction (arXiv:2406.11717) — your "refusal direction" baseline.
    Wollschläger et al., Convergent Linear Representations of Emergent Misalignment (arXiv:2506.11618) — closest to your hypothesis #1.
    Persona Features Control Emergent Misalignment (arXiv:2506.19823) and OpenAI's Toward Understanding and Preventing Misalignment Generalization — closest to your hypothesis #2, and they directly distinguish persona direction from refusal.
    The Delta-Crosscoder paper (arXiv:2603.04426) — does almost exactly your base-vs-misaligned refusal-representation comparison.
    Turner et al., Model Organisms for Emergent Misalignment (~June 2025) — phase-transition detection during fine-tuning, relevant to your "at what point does it break" question.
    https://arxiv.org/pdf/2510.26243

